        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>calcium carbonate white pigment [300218052], transparent white pigment [300013779], white pigment [300013723], pigment by color [300013134], pigments [300013109], colorant (material) [300013026], materials by function [300014692], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An soft, whitish, absorbent powder derived from the siliceous skeletons of microscopic water plants called diatoms, composed of 88% silica. It is used as a poultice, a desiccating insecticide, a decolorizer and filtration aid for purifying oils, fats, and waxes, an inert pigment, a filler in paper, paint, brick, floor tiles, ceramics, linoleum, plastic, soap, and detergent, an insulation for boilers and blast furnaces, as sound insulation, and as a very mild abrasive in metal polishes and toothpaste. It reduces gloss, acts as a suspending agent, increases viscosity, and absorbs dyes well, thus is used as a base for lake colors.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種質軟、吸水的白色粉末，取自構造中有百分之八十八為二氧化矽的微小水生植物－矽藻－的矽質骨骼。可做為泥敷劑、乾燥殺蟲劑、脫色劑、惰性顏料，可用來過濾並淨化油、脂肪及蠟，可當作紙張、油漆、磚塊、地磚、陶瓷、油氈、塑膠、肥皂和清潔劑的填充料，可做為鍋爐和高爐的絕緣體，可當作聲音絕緣體，也可做為金屬擦亮劑和牙膏中非常溫和的研磨劑。矽藻土能降低光澤、當作懸浮劑、增加黏度，並善於吸收染料，因而做為色澱顏料的基底。 </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
